		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="108181953491622"></a><span class="msgSubject">Melee Cleric Revisted</span><br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Melee Cleric Revisted";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Apr 12th  2004 at  9:28pm EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=108181953491622;num=24;page=1;post=1;replyto=108181953491622"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    | <span class="fs8">Edited: Apr 17th  2004 at  2:01am EDT</span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=184366"><span class="Scholar">dfrnchman</span></a><b><span class="Scholar"><br/>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />961 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=108181953491622;page=1;howmany=50#108181953491622"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Yet another example of why Clerics should be allowed to keep up their melee skills and not just expected to sit on thier backside in a fight. I was on an Ldon(high Risk) with a group of fellow low 50's. We had Paladin(Me), Warrior, Monk (FD puller), Beastie, Cleric and Mage. Almost done with adventure and Monk goes to pull. Warrior gets a bit anxious and gets a little to close so that when monk FD's, the MOBs switch to warrior. Oh Great. (Monk had pulled 4 too) <br /> <br />Just after we take the second mob down Cleric crys OOM(He had also cried out KEI faded about 2 minutes earlier, this just gets better and better). People start saying maybe we should run for it. Instead, I cry out out &quot;Cleric take Melee, Ill handle heals (I was fm with LoH still up). Cleric did so(and did some pretty good hits too) and I started Greater Healing as fast As I could (Thank heavens for KEI). We managed to take down the remaining 2 with my 300 hp heals and my burning the LoH. If the cleric had hung back and tried to regen mana, we might not have made it. <br /> <br />So to those of you who STILL believe clerics should do nothing but heal and med, think again. You never know when a cleric with a club can be a big save. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Apr 12 21:27:29 2004 by dfrnchman</span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Apr 17 01:58:47 2004 by dfrnchman</span></i></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Dorboln Crushkiller <br />Officer of &lt;In Via Damnum&gt; <br />Xev Server <br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=911157" title="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=911157" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=911157</a> <br />Mindariax Tamuril <br /><a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=331521105" title="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=331521105" target="akztarg">http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer...d=331521105</a> <br />Kaiyala Telemmaite <br /><a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=331538105" title="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=331538105" target="akztarg">http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer...d=331538105</a> <br />Blackburrow Server</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >24 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
