		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=336663"><span class="">Magyc</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />7 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=108181953491622;page=1;howmany=50#108181953491622"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Dfrnchman,  <br /> <br /> 	Hi, I want to start off by saying, thank you for the piece you wrote on clerics.  It's nice to see someone on my side.   <br />	I'm writing this on behalf of my 4th alt, Phrogglianna.  She is a cleric and just turned 10 today.  I made her a cleric because I have a couple of friends, with 65 level clerics that are fighters and their abilities leave me in awe when I see what they can do.   <br />	Today, someone asked me to group with them.  I made sure they understood that I wouldn't be there for healing purposes due to the fact I was working on melee skills such as offense, defense and evocation rather than alteration.  It was no problem with the group that I did this and the one that asked me to join said they really didn't need a healer anyway.  At one point, I was low on mana, and low on health.  The one I had made the deal with ask why I didn't heal myself.  I told him I was low on mana, plus I could mend while medding.  I was trying not to use my alteration skill too much.  He couldn't understand why I wanted a fighting cleric asking me why didn't I just make a paladin. Right after he stated his opinion, he pulled multi-mobs and the enchanter died (level 8).  Then I died (level 10). The other 2 didn't die, but proceeded to harass me because I let the enchanter die and I wasn't playing my toon right.  I went back to get my body and told him I'm sorry he feels the way he does and hope he has fun, since thats what Everquest is all about.  He said “Wtf are you talking about.”  It's obvious I was dealing with a closed-minded idiot.   <br />	I believe that it is a cleric's job to heal, but I also believe they should be fighters as well.  Also, when people group and they have an understanding of what their groupies would like to accomplish then they should honor it with respect and encouragement.   There is a fine line between constructive criticism and badgering.  People need to learn how to talk to people.  Tact is a wonderful thing.  <br /> <br />		Thank you,  <br /> <br />			Magyc <br /> <br />Magyc Wolf  <br />Lost Wages Druid <br />Xev server <br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=911992" title="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=911992" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=911992</a> <br /> <br />Phrogglianna (4th alt) <br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=938195" title="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=938195" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=938195</a> <br /></p>
