<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Yesterday we almost finished a Rujarkian adventure (lvl 51+). Just one (really big) room left including the boss we had to kill. While trying to make the area clear one of that mobs resisted my pacify and started running to us bringing 4 friends with him - all on me - the cleric. All expected my fast death because we had no real croud control in our group (only a shaman with root and me - but casting while having  5 MOBs on me is &quot;a bit&quot; difficult). So I took several hits while just doing nothing and waiting for at least 2 roots of our shm. During this time our tank and monk and rogue started to get agro from the MOBs. So after a few seconds my HP had gone down to about 20% and I castet Divine Barrier. At this time already 3 MOBS had been rooted and we had only to melee 2 MOBs at once and I started healing. <br /> <br />So as u see: It's really important for a cleric to have the defensive skill maxed to stay at least a few seconds longer against MOBs and give the rest of the group a few seconds to act.</p>
