<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>You have obviously never played a cleric over lvl 55 or so if you think clerics cannot tank.  No, not against extreme high end mobs, but against run-of-the-mill Low to midlevel Dark Blue non-planar mobs?  Oh yes.  Clerics can tank.  We can even hold aggro fairly well on mobs under lvl 55 by chainstunning with the three lowest level stuns. <br /> <br />As a lvl 59 Cleric, with Temperance, Kei, and the next-to-best self-only AC buff, with summoned hammer of Divinity, and no haste equipment, I can easily MELEE solo Velks entry mobs.  These aren't even undead. <br /> <br />Here's how I do it. <br /> <br />1) Pacy-pull a single mob. <br />2) Root mob, Cast Marks of Retribution and Karn on the mob. <br />3) Summon pet (and instantly rush the mob, so you get to mob before pet does) <br />4) Start Cranking out the Yaulp V's, bashing, and swinging that summoned hammer.  Every 45 seconds or so, cast Heal-over-time on self. <br /> <br />No need to nuke, fear, or stun.  No need to med - Yaulp V and Kei keep the mana full, as long as I don't get adds and need to root park. <br /> <br />This can be done without the cleric pet, but it's a pain, because the pet is actually a decent chunk of DPS (as compared to a meleeing cleric anyway :P) <br /> <br /> <br />Aever Naever, Firiona Vie <br />Self-Buffed AC @1000 <br />Self-Buffed HP @2800 <br /></p>
