<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I fully agree with Cheopis. Once a cleric gets Yaulp V and the first decent summoned hammer at level 56 a cleric is a very formidiable tanks. Granted not against Planar or GoD mobs. Just the other night our guild, which has very few upper level tanks scheduled a raid to Kedge Keep for a druid epic piece; however, no tanks showed up. Anyway, since we had a 65 cleric there in addition to me, a 58 cleric, I volunteered to tank. After Virtue and the AC self buff, I had 3800 hp and an AC 1252. Using Yaulp V, bashing and stunning, I was able for the most part hold aggro on the seahorses. <br /> <br />So in conclusion, Yes clerics primary purpose is to Heal, no disagreement there. However, even when they are the Healer in the group they can still provide serious DPS and in a pinch some clerics, not all, can be the MT and be just as effective as a pally.</p>
