<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p> <br />Recipe for Battle Cleric <br /> <br />Three of us regularly pass MM advs running 3man.  We are in our mid 50s.  We have a cleric, myself, an SK and a chanter.  My battle cleric combo:  Dawnfire, a cleric only 1hb that procs 585 against undead along with the improved damage 3 Belt of Reformed Sand.  With a buff combo of Focus and Boon of Garou my usual 92 DEX is maxed.  I switch to SCHW for item haste and the chanty hastes me.  The procs add a very significant amount to DPS, proccing for up to 710ish, often multiple times per undead pull.  <br /> <br />I pull with Annul magic and usually have to CH the tank every 5 fights or so.  With kei running we usually have to stop once for med time.  I med during fights against living mobs. <br /> <br />We wouldn't dream of attempting this on high risk, nor would I recommend attempting such tomfoolery with pickups.  We do this late night when we can't fill out our group to 6.  Strangers usually act very guarded when you ask them to join as a fourth and last party member, but we haven't lost a 4man yet and are about 80% success rate on 3man with very low casualties.  </p>
