<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>My main is a level 65 cleric on Tholuxe Paells, Faddor.  I have actively been meleeing since level 56.  My primary job is to heal, but by using &quot;F&quot; keys and macros to streamline targeting and healing, I do not sacrifice healing.  In most cases I add significant damage for my group. The summoned Hammer of Damnation has a nice proc especially with Nights Dark Terror and some kind of haste.  My guildies know what I can do and more than once have spoken up when closed minded people have told me how to play my character.   <br /> <br />In a few cases I have taken over when we had to split, or had no true tank.  Cleric group heal works really well to keep the group standing while fighting for our lives.  On one recent occasion we had two level 65 clerics, a 65 enchantress, and three lower caster types.  Our mission was to explore new places to take low 60s guild groups.  I tanked the entire expedition and we had no deaths.   <br /> <br />In short, get off your butts clerics, develop your melee skills, upgrade your armor to take a punch, mix it up when you can and be ready to stand in when you need too.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />...I felt the crowd breathe in and I closed my eyes, and we disappeared into the groove.... <br />~Marc Broussard</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8">Posting from Atlanta Georgia</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
