<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I am a 67 level cleric, Simply put clerics are not and never will be tanks. Any cleric who thinks he is in for a big suprise. <br /> <br />Cleric melee skills are however quite useful. With Yaulp VI going in melee I regen mana at a more than acceptable rate in normal situations. I generally melee in assist of MT keeping eye on life levels for heals.  <br /> <br />When caster classes draw agg I can usually hit mob with quick stun to freeze it long enough for tank to regain agg with out a lot of running around. <br /> <br />My wife a 66 shammy and I frequently duo together. Between her slows and my heals we can easily handle mobs in zones up to BoT and HoH. We prefer slightly lower planes though as the increased kill rate delivers more exp in the long run. <br /> <br />A well equipted cleric can take some hits, with slows and added dps can kill some mobs but never think you will have a chance as a tank. <br /> <br /></p>
