<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I see this as a game of role players. Not in the sense of rpg, but that each class has a role to play in their group.  While it may at times be necessary for the cleric to melee, it is definitely not your primary role, nor should it be.  Just because you can get by doing it doesnt mean you should.  In any situation a tank will do a better job tanking than you will as a cleric.  Thats a fact.  I can see where it helps to have high defense, and would like to have my offense and 1hb higher for the situations when i actually do melee.  But unless you are tanking someone's pet for fun or killing lb monsters somewhere i dont see where you have the time to work on those skills often enough to get the skills high.  I think time is better spent working on the skills that make you a worthwhile addition to your group. Namely work on things that will give you mana and mana regen.  If you want to waste time, start your shawl quest.  That will keep you busy for a few months. </p>
