<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Using your logic, EVERY class in the game are tanks. I've had a necro tank riftseekers named. Necros are tanks. I've had a shaman tank in riftseekers. Shaman are tanks. I've had a druid tank in WoS, so druids are tanks. Heck, I've had a bard tank a god in PoTime, so bards are clearly tanks. <br /> <br />Oddly, when I grind, and we are looking for a tank, I never see anyone say, oh look, there is a necro, get him. You know why? Because necros are not tanks. For the same reason, nobody ever says get the cleric when we need a tank. <br /> <br />Yes, a cleric can tank, below their level of gear. I already agreed to this. But, it is not mana efficient, and a cleric CANNOT tank nearly as well as a real tank. The only defensive skill you get is dodge, and it is capped lower. You also have a much lower AC softcap than a tank, or even a monk, ranger or BL. <br /> <br />I would venture to guess you cannot tank the Statue of Rallos Zek. A monk/Ranger or BL in your level of gear can. A plate tank in your level of gear can tank Avatar of War. What, raid mobs you say? nope, easily one groupable at your level of gear. Msha's are one groupable too, but not with a cleric tanking.  <br /> <br />When I say cannot tank, I mean that you cannot perform comparably to a warrior, paladin or shadowknight in the same level of gear. If you feel that what you do makes you a tank, by all means call yourself a tank. But don't be surprised when others don't agree.</p>
